description:
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy now exists at Kingscroft Short Break (respite) Health Service for adults with Learning disabilities for a Team Leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant should be enthusiastic, an effective communicator, have high standards, and be sensitive to the needs of people with learning disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Team Leader you will be responsible for providing training, assessment and guidance on clinical procedures to support workers; supporting staff to deliver high standards of care to the people who use the service. You should have experience of working with adults with learning disabilities and specialist health needs and be motivated to providing a person-centred service. You should be a competent communicator as effective liaison with staff, families and other professional is vital to this role. You should be able to work a flexible shift pattern including weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal enquiry regarding the post please contact: Louise Nicholson on 01784 465134. We look forward to your application.&lt;/p&gt;
